\"Johnny was such a special player and an even better person,\" said Team USA captain Patrick Kane. \"We wanted to make sure we honored his memory and let his family know that he will always be a part of this team.\" 

The team's decision to wear Gaudreau's jersey during the medal ceremony was a powerful symbol of their respect and admiration for the young star. Sarah Gaudreau, who had been married to Johnny for just two years, fought back tears as she watched the team pay tribute to her late husband.

\"It means the world to our family to see Johnny honored in this way,\" she said. \"He loved representing his country and being part of Team USA, and I know he would be so proud to see the team carrying on his legacy.\"

Meagan Gaudreau, Johnny's sister, echoed those sentiments, expressing her gratitude for the team's heartfelt gesture.

\"Johnny was taken from us far too soon, but seeing the team come together to celebrate his life and his passion for the game is truly special,\" she said. \"It's a bittersweet moment, but it's a testament to the impact he had on everyone he met.\"

The Team USA tribute was a powerful reminder of the profound impact that Gaudreau had on the hockey community, and the lasting legacy he will leave behind. As the team celebrated their gold medal victory, they did so with heavy hearts, but also with a deep appreciation for the young star who had inspired them and so many others.

