Investors were caught off guard by the tariff hike, as it came just a week after the Federal Reserve cut interest rates for the first time in a decade. The rate cut had been seen as a positive signal for the economy, but Trump's tariff announcement quickly erased those gains.

\"This is a major blow to the markets,\" said financial analyst Sarah Chen. \"Investors were already on edge due to global growth concerns, and now they're facing the prospect of an even more protracted trade war between the U.S. and China.\"

